The president of the Nigerian Labour Congress (NLC) Ayuba Wabba has hailed President Muahmmad Buhari for signing the African Continental Free Trade Area. Wabba said signing of the bill would help in curbing the issue of smuggling and other vices that affecting the continental free trade agreement. He also said that president Buhari has the consensus of all the stake holders that have participated in the consultation, “it is one consultation that have taken place which everybody was brought to the table, it is how government ought to be.” OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE He noted that the process of consultation with stake holders took more than one year, stating that stakeholders such as “manufacturers association, chambers of commerce and industry, medium and small scale enterprises, labour” participated actively in the deliberation of the AfCFTA. Why Buhari put AU trade deal on hold As AfCFTA kicks off Why Buhari cancelled Rwanda trip-FG Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin